review_blob: 12oz Bottle. Pours a hazy yellow orange. Aroma is pine and citrus quite strong. Taste is very Hoppy, with citrus and pine finish. Overall very good IPA.

On Tap at Brewpub. Aroma is very complex. Appearance is slightly hazy golden. Taste is very bitter with citrus and that unique riwaken hop is very good. Overall one of my all time favorites. Grabbed a Growler for home

On tap at Brewpub. Aroma is citrus and pine. Not as much as the PseudoSue. Appearance is hazy gold, Taste is citrus and pine and grass. Good, but not as good as PseudoSue. My buddy has a mix of Zeelander and PseudoSue called SueZee that was excellent.
On tap at Brewpub. Aroma is very chocolaty and some coffee notes. Appearance is a little hazy and dark brown. Taste is roasted coffee with some caramel at the end. Overall very tasty

On Tap from Brewpub. Aroma is very complex and instantly got my mouth watering. Appearance is slightly hazed yellow orange color with a thin white head. Taste is citrus and pine to start and a bit grassy on the finish. Good complex APA. Overall one of the best APAs Ive ever had. Liked it so much I bought a six pack of Bombers to go.

On Tap from Brewpub. Aroma is very nutty and woody, Appearance is deep golden brown, Taste is very woody, not what I was expecting, but very satisfying. Some caramel and yeast notes too. Overall very good
